---
description: Next.js App Router conventions for pages and components
globs: app/**/*.js,components/**/*.js
---

- Routes live at `app/<route>/page.js`, one page per folder, matching the
  existing pattern (`app/about/page.js`, `app/team/page.js`,
  `app/constitution/page.js`, `app/recommendation/page.js`,
  `app/contact/page.js`). Export `metadata` from each page for
  title/description.
- Shared UI goes in `components/` as PascalCase files (`Header.js`,
  `Footer.js`, `PageBanner.js`, `HeroCarousel.js`, `PersonCard.js`). Reuse
  `PageBanner` for any new top-level page's hero banner instead of writing a
  new one — see any existing page for the usage pattern.
- Default to Server Components. Only add `"use client"` when the component
  needs state, effects, or browser APIs — `components/Header.js` (mobile
  menu state) and `components/HeroCarousel.js` (interval/state) are the
  existing examples of when that's warranted.
- Import shared site content from `lib/data.js` via the `@/lib/data` alias
  (nav links, sponsors, directors, contact info, etc.) rather than inlining
  content directly in page files.
- Use `next/image`, not a raw `<img>` tag. Any external image host must be
  added to `images.remotePatterns` in `next.config.mjs` first — don't
  hotlink from a new domain without doing that.
- Styling is Tailwind utility classes only — no CSS modules, no
  styled-components, no inline `style=` unless there's genuinely no Tailwind
  equivalent (e.g. a computed value). Use the brand theme colors (see
  `project-overview.mdc`) for anything brand-colored.
